      "widgets_values": [
        "A stoic **black Shiba Inu** kneels on one knee in a solemn samurai pose, body upright and composed, with one knee pressed to the ground and the other leg firmly planted before him. He has glossy black fur, cream markings on the muzzle, chest, and cheeks, warm tan accents above the eyes and along the legs, erect triangular ears, dark focused eyes, and a thick curled tail. He wears layered samurai armor with curved plates, tied cords, and guarded shoulders and forearms. In both paws, he grips the hilt of a sword plunged into the earth before him, the blade buried deep in the ground as he bows his head and gazes downward in silence. His expression is calm, stern, and reflective, conveying honor, grief, and quiet resolve.\n\nBehind him stretches a dramatic landscape suited to a classic **ukiyo-e** composition: a rocky cliff overlooking a valley veiled in drifting mist, with distant mountain ridges fading into stylized layers on the horizon. Twisted pine trees cling to the windswept slope, their branches curved elegantly by the wind. Scattered autumn leaves move across the scene in flowing patterns, while worn stone markers and sparse grasses suggest the memory of an ancient battlefield. Above, sweeping clouds arc across the sky in decorative shapes, with bands of soft light breaking through to illuminate the warrior and the land around him. The overall scene should feel noble, melancholic, and grand, with the strong silhouette, balanced composition, and dramatic natural setting of a traditional ukiyo-e print.\n"
      ]
